# Unit Testing Rules

## File Location and Structure
- All test files must be in `/src/components/__tests__/`
- Use `.test.ts` for TypeScript files
- Use `.test.tsx` for React components
- Mirror source file structure
- Example: `schemas.ts` → `schemas.test.ts`

## Test Organization
```typescript
import { describe, it, expect } from '@jest/globals';
import { ComponentName } from '../ComponentName';

describe('ComponentName', () => {
    it('should validate valid data', () => {
        // Test valid case
    });

    it('should reject invalid data', () => {
        // Test invalid case
    });
});
```

## Coverage Requirements
- Minimum 90% coverage for critical files
- Document uncovered lines
- Focus on critical paths
- Test edge cases

## Mocking Rules
- Mock external dependencies
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Reset mocks between tests
- Example for browser APIs:
```typescript
class MockFile {
    fileBits: any[];
    name: string;
    size: number;
    type: string;
    lastModified: number;
    webkitRelativePath: string = '';
    constructor(fileBits: any[] = [], fileName: string = 'mock.txt', options: any = {}) {
        this.fileBits = fileBits;
        this.name = fileName;
        this.size = 0;
        this.type = (options && options.type) || '';
        this.lastModified = (options && options.lastModified) || Date.now();
    }
    slice() { return this; }
}
```

## Common Patterns

### Schema Tests
```typescript
describe('SchemaName', () => {
    it('should validate valid data', () => {
        const validData = { /* valid data */ };
        expect(() => Schema.parse(validData)).not.toThrow();
    });

    it('should reject invalid data', () => {
        const invalidData = { /* invalid data */ };
        expect(() => Schema.parse(invalidData)).toThrow();
    });
});
```

### Function Tests
```typescript
describe('functionName', () => {
    it('should return expected result', () => {
        const result = functionName(input);
        expect(result).toBe(expectedOutput);
    });
});
```

## Running Tests
```bash
# Run all tests
npm test

# Run with coverage
npm test -- --coverage

# Run specific test file
npm test -- --coverage src/components/__tests__/schemas.test.ts
```

## Common Issues

### Browser API Mocks
- Mock at top level
- Include all required properties
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Document mock behavior

### Type Errors
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Avoid `any` where possible
- Use type assertions when necessary
- Document complex types

### Test Isolation
- Reset mocks between tests
- Use `beforeEach` and `afterEach`
- Don't rely on test order
- Keep tests independent


